@kevinskwang 
Since the lockup can cause serious nightly issues, wanted to go ahead and file this to remove that possibility rather than investigate it long-term, especially since these APIs are not typically used and aren't necessary here. 

Ultimately I don't have a good reason why this would sometimes lockup. My best guess is that it somehow kept seeing packets arriving without ever timing out, so it just keeps counting forever. Even the possibility of that happening is a good reason not to mess with this API. I did notice around 20-30% CPU utilization when this happens, suggesting it is constantly parsing packets. 

Here's a link to the potential infinite loop: https://github.com/p4lang/ptf/blob/8e0fdf8b214422ea6db6c6b41042160b9be2d8c3/src/ptf/testutils.py#L3639

PTF API source code cited here:
```python
 while True:
 result = dp_poll(
 test, device_number=device_number, port_number=port, timeout=timeout
 )
 if isinstance(result, test.dataplane.PollSuccess):
 if ptf.dataplane.match_exp_pkt(exp_packet, result.packet):
 total_rcv_pkt_cnt += 1
 else:
 break
```
These PTF testutils while-true statements with conditional exits and no max timeout are pretty concerning.

